    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="178"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d178">
                <head>178. Record of Decisions<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d178fn1">Source:
                        Central Intelligence Agency, Job 79–01025A, Box 71, Folder 6. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-09"
                        >June 9, 1954</date>.</dateline>
                <p rend="center">DECISIONS TAKEN AT <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1"
                        >PBSUCCESS</gloss> MEETING OF 9 JUNE 1954</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>It is understood that <persName>LINCOLN</persName> will give prior notice
                        to Headquarters of the proposed departure of any senior members of <gloss
                            target="#t_LINC1">LINC</gloss> Station to the field, indicating where
                        they are going and for what purposes. (<hi rend="italic">Action</hi>:
                            <persName>LINCOLN</persName>) (In this connection, <gloss
                            target="#t_LINC1">LINC</gloss> is to be advised which countries require
                        the visa applicant to appear in person.) (<hi rend="italic">Action</hi>: Mr.
                            [<hi rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] and Mr.
                            <persName>Preston</persName>)</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Discussion was had of the latest <persName>Corcoran</persName> attacks
                        against the Agency and his efforts to penetrate <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss> and bring pressures to bear,
                        using only slightly veiled threats of stirring up trouble for <gloss
                            target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> on the Hill. Messrs. <persName
                            corresp="#p_BTPWD1">Barnes</persName> and [<hi rend="italic">name not
                            declassified</hi>] were requested to pass the word down the line at
                            <gloss target="#t_LINC1">LINC</gloss> to the effect that no one should
                        have any conversation with or pass any word to <persName>Corcoran</persName>
                        without prior approval of <gloss target="#t_DCI1">DCI</gloss>. This is the
                        Agency line as a whole. (Messrs. [<hi rend="italic">name not
                            declassified</hi>] and <persName corresp="#p_BTPWD1">Barnes</persName>
                        said that they know of no one at or connected with <gloss target="#t_LINC1"
                            >LINC</gloss> who had had any contact with or passed any word to
                            <persName>Corcoran</persName>.) (<hi rend="italic">Action</hi>: Messrs.
                            <persName corresp="#p_BTPWD1">Barnes</persName> and [<hi rend="italic"
                            >name not declassified</hi>])</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Cable is to be sent to [<hi rend="italic">place not declassified</hi>] in
                        an effort to get [<hi rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>]
                        (correspondent there) to write the <persName>Perez Asturias</persName>
                        story. (Action: Mr. [<hi rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>])</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>After the 5:00 meeting with Mr. <persName corresp="#p_DAARA1"
                            >Dulles</persName> today, the problem of the additional radio operators,
                        to be procured from General <persName>McClellan</persName>’s shop, is to be
                        re-examined. (<hi rend="italic">Action</hi>: Mr. <persName
                            corresp="#p_WFHSW1">Wisner</persName>)</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>A cable is to be sent to [<hi rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>]
                        requesting that he cable Hqs at least a preliminary report of the [<hi
                            rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>]/<persName>Perez
                            Jimenez</persName> meeting. Hqs is planning to leak a story re this
                        meeting and it is important that we get the information developed on this
                        meeting. (<hi rend="italic">Action</hi>: Mr. <persName corresp="#p_EJD1"
                            >Esterline</persName>)</item>
                    <label>6.</label>
                    <item>The <gloss target="#t_FOA1">FOA</gloss> plan to be handled with Mr.
                            <persName>Weiland</persName> of USIA. (<hi rend="italic">Action</hi>:
                        Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BRMLPE1">Bissell</persName>)</item>
                </list>
            </div>
